@page "/usage"
<PageTitle>Using Event Timings on Phone or Tablet</PageTitle>

<h1>Using Event Timings on Phone or Tablet</h1>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
        This short guide is focused on phone and tablet users. It explains how to quickly view events, follow live timing, and check results on small screens.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>Quick mobile tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Tap the menu button (the navigation icon) to open pages like <a href="">Timing board</a>, <a href="riders">Riders</a>, and <a href="results">Results</a>.</li>
        <li>Rotate your device to landscape for more horizontal space when selecting riders or using timing controls.</li>
        <li>Use the search box on the Riders page to find a rider by name, bib number, or category.</li>
        <li>To reload live data, pull down to refresh (supported by most mobile browsers) or use the browser reload button.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>Getting started (phone/tablet)</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open the app in your mobile browser.</li>
        <li>Optional: add a shortcut to your home screen for quick access (your browser may prompt to "Add to Home screen").</li>
        <li>Tap the menu and choose the page you need.</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>Common mobile tasks</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>View a rider:</strong> Menu → Riders → tap the rider's name to see details.</li>
        <li><strong>Follow live timing:</strong> Menu → Timing board. Officials: sign in at the top of the Timing board (enter Name and PIN), select a rider, then tap <em>Start</em> or <em>Stop</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>View results:</strong> Menu → Results. Use the search or filters if available.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>Troubleshooting on mobile</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>If a page is blank or out of date, try pulling down to refresh or tap the browser reload button.</li>
        <li>Switch browsers (Chrome, Safari, Edge) if a page won't load correctly.</li>
        <li>If live updates stop, check your internet connection and reopen the app.</li>
        <li>Close other tabs or background apps if the device feels slow.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <h2>FAQs (mobile)</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>Q:</strong> Can I time riders from my phone?<br />
        <strong>A:</strong> Yes. Officials can use the Timing board to start and stop timing; rotating to landscape often makes controls easier to tap.
    </p>
</section>

